<br>
Theist: A person who believes in a God or higher power and also believes that that God plays an active role in the world at large (miracles, and examples of other holy events).<br>
<br>
Deist: A person who believes in a God or higher power, but also believes that that God or power has left man to his own devices, and will return to Judge man based on what they did once everything is over.<br>
<br>
Bear in mind these are VERY VERY bare bones definitions of these three schools of religious thoughts.<br>
<br>
Also on a note... I was FAR FAR FAR from bashing Christianity.  I proud to be a Christian... I am an Episcopalian.  However, I believe that religion is a very personal and private thing... and I take great offense when people attempt to ram it down my throat or the throat of others.  <br>
<br>
