<br>
First of all, the few men who wrote the documents might have been simply diests, but the core of america, is, and has been from the beginning, a very christian(Mostly protestant) nation.<br>
<br>
Papists(catholics) were, at the least, looked down upon(at the most, it was illegal for a catholic to own land in the colonies) at the beginning of our nation.  The Quakers were looked at oddly, and witches were still burned at the stake(along with anyone else they could throw to the flames, but that part's neither here, nor there.)<br>
<br>
Joseph Smith(founder of the mormon church) was run out of town, thrown in jail, beaten, and generally illtreated because of the religion he started in the early 1800's(I think that's the right dates. Been too long since I saw church haha)<br>
<br>
And from them to now, from the southern slaves that were mostly expected to be at the very least &quot;ignorant heathens&quot; to the teenager in today's high schools not allowed to wear a pentagram around his neck, while the guy in the next seat gets to wear his tribute to the brutal murder of christ, this country is a christian nation in deed, if not in word. <p><center><i><b><a href="http://chickstuff.blogspot.com/" target="_new">Traelle</a></b></i>
